parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause the brakes to overheat, leading to a loss of braking performance, increased stopping distance, and potentially accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal extends to the floorboard
the brakes lock intermittently
the brakes are slow to stop
fluid leaks from the brakes onto the tires and wheels
the brakes are dragging
and the brake pads are burning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to a loss of braking performance, increased stopping distance, and potentially accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes are slow to stop
fluid leaks from the brakes onto the tires and wheels
and the brakes are dragging.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pads can cause the brakes to overheat, leading to a loss of braking performance, increased stopping distance, and potentially accidents.
symptoms: The brake pads are burning
the brakes are slow to stop
and the brakes are dragging.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tail light assembly can cause a loss of visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions. Additionally, the sudden loss of tail lights can lead to rear-end collisions.
symptoms: The tail light lens is melting
the tail light assembly falls off
the tail lights fail to function without warning
water or weather conditions cause a short in the bulb.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Insufficient Mounting of Tail Light Assembly
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The insufficient mounting of the tail light assembly can cause it to fall off, leading to a loss of visibility and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The tail light assembly falls off
the mounting bolts are small or insufficient
the tail light assembly is not properly secured.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The abnormal fogging of the front dual pane windows can significantly reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents and compromising road safety.
symptoms: Fogging or misting on the front dual pane windows
reduced visibility
obscured driver-side mirror.
